hopobject.body: I've got a very weak signal rogaine foam results timeline Look at, say, life expectancy at the state level and the variations are massive. It’s 81 years in Hawaii. It’s 76 in Kentucky. 81 is well above the OECD average, and light years above Kentucky’s. Are you seriously prepared to make the claim that doctors and hospitals in Kentucky are so inferior, or in Hawaii are so superior, that discrepancies in the clinical efficacy of the care they deliver account for all, or even some of the differences in life-expectancy or any other health-status metric? Really?
